---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for National Nines Golf website - how we handle your personal data.">
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl font-bold text-brand-black mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: January 2026</p>
        
        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          National Nines Golf Ltd ("we", "us", "our") operates the website nationalninesgolf.co.uk. 
          We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your personal data responsibly.
        </p>
        
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect information you provide directly to us, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Competition entries:</strong> Names, email addresses, phone numbers, club membership, and handicap information</li>
          <li><strong>Shop purchases:</strong> Name, email, phone, delivery address, and payment information</li>
          <li><strong>Contact forms:</strong> Name, email, and message content</li>
          <li><strong>Newsletter sign-ups:</strong> Email address and preferences</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Process competition entries and manage events</li>
          <li>Fulfill shop orders and arrange delivery/collection</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about your entries or orders</li>
          <li>Send marketing communications (only with your consent)</li>
          <li>Improve our services and website</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>4. Payment Processing</h2>
        <p>
          We use Stripe to process payments securely. Your payment card details are handled directly by Stripe 
          and are never stored on our servers. Please refer to <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank">Stripe's Privacy Policy</a> 
          for information on how they handle your data.
        </p>
        
        <h2>5. Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p>We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Golf clubs:</strong> Entry details shared with host venues for event administration</li>
          <li><strong>Delivery services:</strong> Address details for shipping orders</li>
          <li><strong>Payment processors:</strong> Stripe for secure payment handling</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We never sell your personal data to third parties.</p>
        
        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, 
          comply with legal obligations, and resolve disputes. Competition records may be kept for 
          historical and statistical purposes.
        </p>
        
        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses essential cookies to enable basic functionality like shopping cart storage. 
          We do not use tracking or advertising cookies.
        </p>
        
        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this privacy policy or your personal data, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@nationalninesgolf.co.uk">info@nationalninesgolf.co.uk</a><br />
          Phone: 07818 400286
        </p>
        
        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant 
          changes by posting the new policy on this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .font-heading { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; }
  .text-brand-black { color: #1a1a1a; }
  
  .prose h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .prose p, .prose li {
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  
  .prose ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .prose a {
    color: #c41e3a;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
